All the information on Enjoy Food is written and approved by highly qualified,
registered dietitians who translate the latest public and scientific research
into practical guidance to help people make healthy food choices.
All our tips, recipes and advice will support the work you do with your own
dietitian, who will tailor an eating-plan to your individual needs.
People with diabetes should see a dietitian as soon as they are diagnosed and
have regular, on-going reviews. If you haven’t seen a dietitian yet, ask your
Our advice is to eat a healthy, balanced diet – which involves eating a
variety of foods from each of the main food groups. The advice we give is
based on scientific evidence that is widely accepted as being effective and
safe long term. We recognise other diets, such as low-carb and low-calorie,
exist but believe that to safely follow these you need to involve your
All the advice we give is general – your dietitian can give you more personal
information as they will have detailed access to you and your medical history.
Someone is diagnosed with diabetes every two minutes. Your donation can change
